    "number": 2332,
    "state": "closed",
    "locked": false,
    "title": "[cutlass] Allow compilation of cutlass FA3 for sm100 via enable_sm90",
    "user": {
      "login": "henrylhtsang",
      "id": 91030427,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjkxMDMwNDI3",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/91030427?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/henrylhtsang",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/following{/other_user}",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/gists{/gist_id}",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/starred{/owner}{/repo}",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/events{/privacy}",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/henrylhtsang/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "user_view_type": "public",
      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "Rename enable_sm90_or_later to enable_sm90 and restrict the arch guard from `__CUDA_ARCH__ == 900` to `__CUDA_ARCH__ == 900`.\r\n\r\nFA3's sm90 kernels use CUTLASS GMMA (wgmma) instructions that are gated behind CUTE_ARCH_MMA_SM90A_ENABLED, which requires `__CUDA_ARCH__ == 900` (exact match). On sm100 (Blackwell), these instructions are not available and the code paths fall into CUTE_INVALID_CONTROL_PATH traps.\r\n\r\nBy restricting the guard to == 900, the kernel body becomes dead code on sm100, allowing FA3 to compile cleanly for all default architectures (sm80 + sm90a + sm100a) in a single fat binary without needing to hardcode -gencode flags. This mirrors the existing enable_sm80_to_sm89 pattern.",
    "created_at": "2026-03-12T03:32:39Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-03-12T12:28:55Z",
